<TITLE>Trade-offs #158</TITLE>
<BODY>

<H2>Trade-offs</H2>

Economics for Intermediate and Junior High<P>

<B>Trade-offs</B> is designed to help students think through economic problems and increase their understanding of economics. Each program considers a fundamental economic problem relevant to the daily life of the child, emphasizes the economic principles and reasoning processes involved in dealing with the problem, and introduces similar problems to stimulate classroom discussion and follow-up activities.<P>

<B>Trade-offs</B> was developed jointly by AIT, Canadian Foundation for Economic Education, Joint Council on Economic Education, and a consortium of state and provincial agencies with financial assistance from 14 foundations and corporations. Produced for AIT by Educational Film Center (formerly NVETA), Annandale, Virginia; TVOntario, Toronto; and KERA, Dallas (1978).<P>

<H3>Purchase</H3>
<TABLE>           
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD>Standard</TD><TD>Consortium</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Each Program</TD><TD></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>$150.00</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>$105.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Series</TD><TD>(#158-VVV)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>1,795.00</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>1,275.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>VideoKit&reg;</TD><TD>(#158-VK)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>600.00</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>550.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Teacher's Guide</TD><TD>(#158-TG)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>5.50</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>5.50</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>

