<HTML>
<TITLE>The U.S. Constitution #251</TITLE>
<BODY>

<H2>The U.S. Constitution</H2>

Government, Civics, and History for Grades 7-12<P>

Examine how this 200-year-old document affects the rights of all citizens, even those under voting age. Show students why the U.S. Constitution is an enduring and fundamental document in the American heritage and in their own lives.<P>

Award-winning journalist Bill Moyers explains how the Constitution has been interpreted over the years and how it has evolved to resolve conflict through changing political, economic, and social situations. Dramatic segments present recurring constitutional themes and issues that help young people understand and appreciate the Constitution's application to their daily lives.<P>

<B>The U.S. Constitution</B> was developed in association with Project '87 through the resources of a consortium of state education agencies, organized and managed by AIT, with partial funding from Exxon Education Foundation (1987).<P>

<H3>Purchase</H3>
(standard and consortium member prices)<BR>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD>Each Program</TD><TD></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>$180.00</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>$130.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Series</TD><TD>(#251-VVV)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>895.00</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>650.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>VideoKit&reg;</TD><TD>(#251-VKO)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>525.00</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>470.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Teacher's Guide</TD><TD>(#251-TG)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>5.25</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>

<TABLE>
<TR><TD>VIDEO</TD><TD>Six 30-minute programs</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>PRINT</TD><TD>44-page teacher's guide</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>&nbsp;</TD><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD>WINNER</TD><TD>AECT Recognition Award (1987)</TD></TR>
