<TITLE>Well, Well, Well #239</TITLE>
<BODY>

<H2>Well, Well, Well with Slim Goodbody</H2>

Physical Health and Wellness for Kindergarten-Grade 4<P>

Explore how having a positive mental attitude, accepting your feelings, and practicing healthy habits all contribute to a healthy life. Help young students understand the concept of "wellness," learn ways of caring for the mind and body, and develop self-respect.<P>

Slim Goodbody, along with his friends General Health, Professor U.B. Schmart, and Hairy T. Sludge encourage children to take an active part in protecting, maintaining, and improving their own good health. By emphasizing wellness, safety, nutrition, exercise, and handling feelings in a healthy way, Slim helps students realize that choices made now will affect them the rest of their lives.<P>

<B>Well, Well, Well with Slim Goodbody</B> was produced by AIT (1985).<P>

<H3>Purchase</H3>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD>Each Program</TD><TD></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>$125.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Series</TD><TD>(#239-VVV)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>995.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>VideoKit&reg;</TD><TD>(#239-VKO)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>525.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Teacher's Guide</TD><TD>(#349-TG)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>5.25</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>

<TABLE>
<TR><TD>VIDEO</TD><TD>Fifteen 15-minute programs</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>PRINT</TD><TD>32-page teacher's guide</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>

Save over 45%. Purchase the complete <B>Well, Well, Well</B> series for only $995.<P>

<H3>Programs</H3>

<B>Wellness</B><BR>
Explain that wellness means total good health and introduce students to the five areas of wellness: physical, intellectual, emotional, social, and spiritual. Students learn that their bodies will work better if they take care of themselves.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-001</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Go, Grow, Glow</B><BR>
Identify food as the body's source of energy for activity and growth. Explain why it is important to chew food well. Introduce digestion as the process that prepares food for the body to use.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-002</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Food Power</B><BR>
Demonstrate how eating a variety of foods helps keep the body healthy. Explain why it is important to eat a good breakfast and identify the Famous Food Group Plan as a way to choose a balanced variety of foods.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-003</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Clean Power</B><BR>
Describe why cleanliness is a good health practice for guarding against germs. Help students become responsible for caring for their own bodies--keeping them clean and well groomed--and explain why it is important to floss the teeth.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-004</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Exercise to Energize</B><BR>
Illustrate that regular exercise helps keep the body healthy and strong. Discuss why it is important to do warm-up and cool-down exercises and distinguish between good and bad posture.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-005</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Relax</B><BR>
Explore how sleep and relaxation help keep the body fit and able to cope with stress. Describe what happens to the body during sleep, explain circumstances that can cause stress, and identify relaxation as a good way to relieve stress.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-006</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Feeling Good</B><BR>
Demonstrate that learning to use your mind, express feelings, and solve problems is part of growing up. Introduce ways to help the mind grow, identify several feelings and tell what might cause them.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-007</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Senses</B><BR>
Study how the senses send messages to the brain about the world around us. Identify the senses as the way we learn about the world, name what we learn about the world from each of the five main senses, and describe ways to protect the sense of sight.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-008</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>You Are Special</B><BR>
Discover why each individual is special because of his or her unique character. Identify traits that make a person special and discuss things friends do for one another.
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-009</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Safety Counts</B><BR>
Witness how indoor safety rules and habits can help prevent accidents and injuries. List three rules for indoor safety, identify dangerous situations commonly found around the home and explain how to correct them, and describe the importance of having a home fire escape plan.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-010</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Play It Safe</B><BR>
Illustrate that outside safety rules and habits can prevent accidents and injuries. Give examples of two or more things to check before biking, describe how to be safe when riding in a car, and identify rules that can help prevent injury from strangers.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-011</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Emergencies</B><BR>
Demonstrate why it is important to know how to get the right help when emergencies happen. Define "emergency," identify appropriate sources of help for two or more emergencies, and describe the kind of help ambulance squad paramedics give.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-012</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Healing Helpers</B><BR>
Explain that when the body is injured or sick, it may require first aid or medicine. Describe first aid for a simple scrape and identify ways medicines help the body. Explain why medicine is not always the best way to help the body feel better and identify safe ways to handle medicines.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-013</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>The Wellness Team</B><BR>
Introduce doctors as people who help us keep our bodies healthy. Help students recognize how each of them and their doctor is a wellness team, explain things to expect in a wellness checkup, and identify things they can do to avoid catching germs or giving them to others.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-014</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Sharing Your World</B><BR>
Illustrate how we all share the responsibility for keeping our community healthy. Identify members of a community's wellness team and tell how they help the community. Show students how they are responsible for keeping the community clean and healthy and explain how recycling can help reduce pollution and save resources.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#239-015</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<HR>
"These highly professional and well-designed programs are quick-paced and as entertaining for adults as they are for their intended audience-young children."<P>

"Curriculum Review"
<HR><P>

