<HTML>
<TITLE>Women in Science #283</TITLE>
<BODY>

<H2>Women in Science</H2>

Career Development for Grades 7-10, Inservice Educators<P>

Encourage women to pursue careers in science. Illustrate the importance of mathematics and science in preparation for a future in science-related careers. Address the barriers that have traditionally discouraged women from seeking careers in science.<P>

Introduce all students to the opportunities for careers in science. Visit over 40 women scientists on the job. These role models discuss their work, career decisions, training, financing their education, and how they meet the demands of a professional life while enjoying family life and personal interests. Meet women from a variety of professional and personal lifestyles, ages, education levels, and ethnic backgrounds.<P>

<B>Women in Science</B> was produced by University of Michigan School of Dentistry with a grant from the U.S. Department of Education, Women's Equity Act Program (1984).<P>

<H3>Purchase</H3>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD>Each Program</TD><TD></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>$150.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Series</TD><TD>(#283-VVV)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>795.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Resource Guide</TD><TD>(#283-TG)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>7.50</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>

<TABLE>
<TR><TD>VIDEO</TD><TD>Seven 30-minute programs</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>One 40-minute program</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>PRINT</TD><TD>80-page resource guide</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>

Save over $400 when you purchase the complete <B>Women in Science</B> series.<P>

<H3>Programs</H3>

<B>Biomedical Fields: Careers for Women</B><BR>
Investigate the rewards of research, the excitement of discovery, and the satisfaction of working to improve the health of others. Meet a genetic toxicologist, an industrial hygienist, a bioengineering student, a student in nuclear medicine, an obstetrician, an endocrinologist, and a pathologist.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#283-001</TD><TD>30-minute video program</TD><TD>$150</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Chemistry: Careers for Women</B><BR>
Demonstrate the satisfaction and excitement of working in a creative, challenging field in which important, life-enhancing discoveries are made. Meet an inorganic chemist, a forensic chemist, the head of a university chemistry department, and the marketing director of a pharmaceutical company.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#283-002</TD><TD>30-minute video program</TD><TD>$150</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Computer Science: Careers for Women</B><BR>
Examine the rewards and challenges of solving problems with computers. Meet a scientific programmer, a systems analyst, a data processing coordinator, an entrepreneur, a computer graphics specialist, a university professor, and a college senior majoring in computer science.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#283-003</TD><TD>30-minute video program</TD><TD>$150</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Dentistry: Careers for Women</B><BR>
Discover the professional and personal rewards that accompany a career in dentistry. Meet a recent graduate in general practice, a recent graduate in a private clinic, a pedodontist and professor of dentistry, a periodontist in private practice and her two daughters in dental school.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#283-004</TD><TD>30-minute video program</TD><TD>$150</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Engineering: Careers for Women</B><BR>
Explore the many aspects of a career in engineering: daily responsibilities, the importance of communication, training, and academic experience. Meet a civil engineer, an electrical engineer, a telecommunications engineer, a professor of computer engineering, and three engineering students.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#283-005</TD><TD>30-minute video program</TD><TD>$150</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Geosciences: Careers for Women</B><BR>
Investigate the rewards of exploring the earth: the opportunities to work outdoors, the variety and excitement of exploration and discovery. Meet a seismologist, an exploration geologist, an internationally known geoscientist, a doctoral student in paleontology, and two geology students.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#283-006</TD><TD>30-minute video program</TD><TD>$150</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Physics and Astronomy: Careers for Women</B><BR>
Observe the creative possibilities and excitement of making new discoveries, finding solutions to difficult problems, and asking questions about the nature of the universe. Meet a theoretical physicist, a U.S. Navy physicist, a nuclear physicist, an award-winning high school physics teacher, an astronomy professor, and two physics students.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#283-007</TD><TD>30-minute video program</TD><TD>$150</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Scientific Careers for Women: Doors to the Future</B><BR>

Role models address barriers that discourage young women from careers in science, identify misconceptions about women in science, and suggest strategies to help women succeed. Recommended for teachers, counselors, parents, and others who influence student career choices.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#283-008</TD><TD>30-minute video program</TD><TD>$150</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<HR>
"[<B>Women in Science</B>] is highly recommended as an accurate portrayal of how women should pursue their scientific aspirations and what they should expect during their pursuits."<P>

"Science Books & Films"
