<HTML>
<TITLE>Wordscape #303</TITLE>
<BODY>

<H2>Wordscape</H2>

Communication Skills and Vocabulary Building for Grades 4-6<P>

Expand students' vocabularies by teaching them to recognize word "cells" as the major building blocks of English words. Help students develop and maintain positive attitudes toward the diversity, utility, and wonder of language.<P>

As students in grades 4-6 begin changing their views of how English is built, they shift from a letter-by-letter or sound-by-sound process to one that focuses on larger units of language--roots, prefixes, and suffixes. Words come alive by demonstrating topic vocabulary used in context through vignettes and explanation. Students see and hear vocabulary in authentic settings, instead of simply "memorizing" a list.<P>

<B>Wordscape</B> explores the multicultural contributions to English vocabulary from Latin, Greek, French, German, Hispanic, West African, and Native American sources.<P>
<B>Wordscape</B> was produced by AIT in association with Oklahoma Educational Television Authority (1990).<P>

<H2>Purchase</H2>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD>Each Program</TD><TD></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>$125.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Series</TD><TD>(#303-VVV)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>995.00</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Teacher's Guide</TD><TD>(#303-TG)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>5.50</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>

<TABLE>
<TR><TD>VIDEO</TD><TD>Sixteen 15-minute programs</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>PRINT</TD><TD>56-page teacher's guide</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Closed Captioned</TD><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD>&nbsp;</TD><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD>WINNER</TD><TD>Heartland Regional Emmy Award for Outstanding  Youth/Children's Program</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Colorado Chapter of the National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences (1991)</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>

Save over 50%. Purchase the complete <B>Wordscape</B> series for only $995.<P>

<H3>Programs</H3>

<B>Building Words</B><BR>
Words about building and buildings are used to introduce the idea that words are "built" of cells. Demonstrate that a word's meaning can vary with its use--it may be a noun in one case, an adjective in another--and how affixes extend the meanings of word cells.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-001</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Movie Words</B><BR>
Focus on word cells about motion and action. Illustrates word meanings with footage from silent films, and scenarios about acting and going to the movies. Reinforce pronunciation and usage through entertaining scenarios, and stress that a word can have different meanings in different situations.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-002</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Words of Time</B><BR>
Words related to time are emphasized in humorous, realistic scenarios involving weekends, music, sports, and other activities, reinforcing correct pronunciation and usage. Old English, Latin, and Greek word cells for time concepts are also presented. 
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-003</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Sports Words</B><BR>
Word cells used in sports to describe body parts, conditions, and actions are highlighted. Spectator and participatory sports scenarios show actors pronouncing and using words in context, combining word cells, and illustrating shifts in meaning.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-004</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Talk Words</B><BR>
Word cells concerned with talk are examined, pointing out how meanings of word cells can shift through time or usage and may eventually seem quite different from their origins. Introduces the dictionary as both an example of a "talk word" and a source for learning more about words. <BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-005</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Food Words</B><BR>
Feature the English and foreign language histories of word cells related to food and eating, as well as the multiple meanings of words formed of these cells. Humorous scenarios let viewers hear words in context.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-006</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Mystery Words</B><BR>
"Mystery words" about hiding, finding, seeing, and not seeing are revealed through suspenseful scenarios that acquaint students with pronunciation and usage in context.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-007</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Loud Talk</B><BR>
Explore definitions and demonstrations of a number of word cells related to loud talk through a series of vignettes. Classical, Old English, and Native American origins of some familiar words are emphasized. Dictionary use is also reinforced.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-008</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Clothing Words</B><BR>
All kinds of clothing and the way people use them shape this program in which scenarios both reinforce usage and pronunciation. Discuss the foreign origins of many clothing terms and the ways in which words change as they travel from language to language.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-009</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Words of Leadership</B><BR>
Lead students through word cells relating to leadership and leaders, using familiar and humorous scenarios to define and model pronunciation of words. Explore some interesting non-English word origins.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-010</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Words of Space</B><BR>
Poetry, scenarios, footage of the night sky, historical illustrations, and the technology of space exploration highlight word cells having to do with heavenly bodies. Discuss Latin, Greek, and Old English roots.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-011</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Writing Words</B><BR>
Present the language of writing and background information on the history of writing through a series of vignettes. A mini-documentary features S.E. Hinton, popular writer of adolescent books.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-012</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Friendship Words</B><BR>
Emphasize word cells related to friendship, society, and companionship. Several scenarios about history, sports, and dating demonstrate usage and pronunciation of words.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-013</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Words of Music</B><BR>
Music and word cells associated with music are used to explore the background, pronunciation, and usage of musical terminology, including the names of some familiar instruments.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-014</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>Animal Words</B><BR>
Examine interesting animal names made of combined word cells, as well as Latinate general terms describing animal characteristics and behaviors. Scenarios provide contextualized usage and pronunciation of words and word cells.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-015</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

<B>A Family of Words</B><BR>
Focus on words and word cells about home, family, and nation. Scenarios emphasize names as well as people's relationships to one another and to their country, illustrating how the words are used and pronounced.<BR>
<TABLE><TR><TD>#303-016</TD><TD>15-minute video program</TD><TD>$125</TD></TR></TABLE><P>

