<HTML>
<TITLE>Your Choice . . . Our Chance #289</TITLE>
<BODY>

<H2>Your Choice . . . Our Chance</H2>

Abuse Prevention, Drug Prevention Education, and Life Coping Skills for Grades 5-6, Adult<P>

Establish drug abuse prevention skills before children become users of tobacco, alcohol, marijuana, or other drugs. Bring together schools, families, and communities into a working partnership for preventing drug use by students in the vulnerable preteen years.<P>

The <B>Your Choice . . . Our Chance</B> school component focuses on knowledge, attitudes, and behaviors that influence drug use, because it is easier to prevent risky health behaviors than it is to change them. The community component features effective prevention and intervention efforts in three very different communities that provide useful, adaptable models for local prevention activities with parents and other adults who want to protect young people from the pressure to turn to drugs.<P>

<B>Your Choice . . . Our Chance</B> was developed in cooperation with the Association for the Advancement of Health Education (AAHE) by a consortium of state and provincial agencies organized and managed by AIT (1990).<P>

Note: Duplication rights are not available for this series.<P>

<B>Your Choice . . . Our Chance</B> has been adopted by Health and Welfare Canada on behalf of all provinces and territories.<P>

<H3>Purchase</H3>
