<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Corporate Profile--Strategic Alliances</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>

<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>

<H1><I>Corporate Profile&#151;</I></H1>
<HR>
<H1 align=center><I>Strategic Alliances</I></H1>
<BR>

<TABLE width="20%" align=right border cellpadding=10>
<TR><TD align=center><FONT color="780000"><B>
Joint financing<HR width=50>
Multimedia projects<HR width=50>
Development & marketing<HR width=50>
Instructional products<HR width=50>
Original programming<HR width=50>
Pooled resources
</B></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="drop_b.gif" ALIGN=LEFT>y working in close cooperation with a growing number of strategic partners, AIT strengthens its ability to develop and market educational programs.  These partners include corporate partners such as Ameritech, educational institutions such as Phi Delta Kappa, and publishers such as South-Western Educational Publishing.  Forming strategic alliances benefits both AIT and its partners.  It allows each partner to contribute and share specialized resources and expertise to reach goals that would not be achievable by a single entity.</P>

<P>Our relationship with Phi Delta Kappa (PDK), for example, gives AIT access to leading writers, theorists, and educators in the areas of teacher training and teacher development.  A recent project with PDK resulted in <I>Education Under Fire</I> and <I>Positive Insights on Education</I>, two series with twelve video programs featuring prominent authors, teachers, and educational leaders, including Henry Levin, Robert Coles, and Carol Shakeshaft.</P>

<P>Similar ventures include projects with the National Council on Economic Education, the Center for Civic Education, and two consortia of state departments of education to develop multimedia curricula that support the teaching of economics and civics.    Cooperation with companies such as Ameritech promise to broaden the exposure and increase the sales of our programs through an innovative series of 2-way video field trips to various workplaces.</P>

<P>South-Western Educational Publishing works closely with us on a variety of educational publishing projects.  Three examples under development are two additional modules for the popular <I>Communication 2000</I> product, three modules on <I>Communication in Careers</I>,  and ten modules for <I>Science Links</I>.  These multimedia instructional products will set a new standard for applied communication resources for eleventh- and twelfth-grade students, and integrated science materials for ninth-grade students.  We create and develop the products; South-Western handles financing, production, marketing, and promotion of finished materials.  Additionally , both AIT and South-Western conduct product-related workshops.  As a major textbook publisher, South-Western is particularly experienced in the often complex textbook adoption process and helps us make the most effective presentation of AIT materials to state education departments.</P>




<TABLE align=right>
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="/profile/sa_blbox.gif"><IMG SRC="/profile/meeting.jpg">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<BR clear=right>

