<HEAD>
<TITLE>Corporate Profile--Emerging Technologies</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>

<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>

<H1><I>Corporate Profile&#151;</I></H1>
<HR>
<H1 align=center><I>Emerging Technologies</I></H1>
<BR>

<TABLE width="20%" align=right border cellpadding=10>
<TR><TD align=center><FONT color="780000"><B>
Integration of instructional media<HR width=50>
Redifining classroom TV<HR width=50>
Advancing the curriculum<HR width=50>
Interactive videodiscs<HR width=50>
Built-in assessments and standards<HR width=50>
Leaders in educational technology
</B></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="drop_s.gif" ALIGN=LEFT>tudents learn best when they are presented with lively and challenging information and when material is relevant to their own lives.  For more than thirty years, AIT has provided educators with instructional materials that are interesting and relevant &#151; and equitable in their treatment of students.  Our goal is to provide technological programming that is blind to differences in gender, race, socioeconomic background, and age.</P>

<P>Today, AIT materials help to define and expand the curriculum in classrooms in the United States and abroad.  Our products have expanded to include nearly 3,500 video programs, interactive videodiscs, CD-ROM, computer software, and extensive print materials.  These resources include series designed to be used with large classes, in small groups, and by individuals.</P>

<P>We were one of the pioneers in the use of classroom TV and have constantly redefined its use to keep pace with changes in technology, educational theory, and classroom requirements.  AIT has maintained a leadership role by integrating increasingly sophisticated technologies with solid instructional design.  <I>Economics at Work</I>, our multimedia economics series for senior high school students, demonstrates the range of resources we offer today in a single series.  The core of the curriculum is five teacher guides and five student guides.  They are supported by five interactive videodiscs which combine drama and documentaries with a data base of commonly used economics charts and graphs, and a software program which allows students to engage in business simulations in seven career clusters.</P>

<P><I>Communication 2000</I> has ten instructor guides and ten learner guides, ten interactive videodiscs, and computer-based templates to help students develop and apply writing skills.  The series encompasses six categories of lessons and incorporates nearly thirty works of literature, ranging from articles and poems to selections from books, all with original illustrations.  Most of the literature selections have been recorded on audio cassettes by professional readers, or, in some cases, the original author.</P>

<TABLE align=left>
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="/profile/et_blbox.gif"><IMG SRC="/profile/compgirl.jpg">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P>As new technologies are proven effective, AIT is making them available in the classroom.  These technologies are already enabling us to offer more integral standards and assessments as components of our programs.  <I>Media Mates</I> represents a unique packaging of proven AIT video titles with related and supporting CD-ROMs developed by CLEARVUE/eav.  Along with the AIT-prepared print, each topic specific <I>Media Mate</I>, whether on cell biology or the industrial revolution,  allows teachers to have a complete media resource in their classrooms, one that is appropriate for  both large group and individualized instruction.</P>


<BR clear=left>
<HR>

<CENTER><TABLE cellpadding=25>
<TR><TD><FONT SIZE="+1"><I>
<IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif"><A HREF="/profile/open.htm">Opening Statement</A><BR>
