<HEAD>
<TITLE>Corporate Profile--Professional Development</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>

<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>

<H1><I>Corporate Profile&#151;</I></H1>
<HR>
<H1 align=center><I>Professional Development</I></H1>
<BR>

<TABLE width="20%" align=right border cellpadding=10>
<TR><TD align=center><FONT color="780000"><B>
Teacher education programs<HR width=50>
Video-based instruction<HR width=50>
Extensive products & services<HR width=50>
Elementary, secondary, post-secondary<HR width=50>
Building educational expertise<HR width=50>
On-site workshops & classes
</B></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="drop_p.gif" ALIGN=LEFT>rofessional educators are expected to keep up with all of the latest theories and findings in a constantly changing and evolving field.  To help them do so, AIT is placing increased emphasis on creating resources that support professional development for teachers and administrators, as well as for involved community members, such as school trustees and parent and community groups.  Many of our recent educational programs also include a substantial staff development component.</P>

<P>We currently offer twenty-two professional development resources that consist of video, print, and videodisc materials.  A recent example is <I>Every Child Can Succeed</I>, a comprehensive print and video toolkit for reforming and restructuring schools.  Developed with the support of the Council of Chief State School Officers and a consortium of state and regional education agencies, the program&#146;s premise is that chronic underachievement can be transformed into success for all children, even those most at risk of failure.  Seventeen video programs and accompanying print materials focus particularly on elementary schools and instructional programs proven successful with disadvantaged children.</P>

<P>As part of our ongoing commitment to teachers who use AIT materials, we also offer a growing array of on-site workshops and classes.  Our professional trainers provide up to two days of instruction on integrating AIT materials into an existing curriculum.  They also provide technical training in how to use new technologies &#151; particularly those with interactive features that increase learning greatly, such as videodisc players and computer software.</P>

<TABLE align=left>
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="/profile/pd_blbox.gif"><IMG SRC="/profile/comphelp.jpg">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P>During 1993, our first full year of formal professional development programs, AIT trained more than 2,000 teachers in site-based sessions in all fifty states.  The programs are available in Canada as well.  Most of them include a follow-up component, in which we return the following year to further refine program skills and prepare the original group to pass on what they&#146;ve learned to other teachers.</P>

<BR clear=left>
<HR>

<CENTER><TABLE cellpadding=25>
<TR><TD><FONT SIZE="+1"><I>
