<HEAD>
<TITLE>Corporate Profile--School-to-Work Transition</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>

<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>

<H1><I>Corporate Profile&#151;</I></H1>
<HR>
<H1 align=center><I>School-to-Work Transition</I></H1>
<BR>

<TABLE width="20%" align=right border cellpadding=10>
<TR><TD align=center><FONT color="780000"><B>
Self-management & teamwork<HR width=50>
Technical competence & job readiness<HR width=50>
Interactive work-related materials<HR width=50>
Building problem-solving skills<HR width=50>
Working in multicultural environments<HR width=50>
Training for  the future
</B></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="drop_e.gif" ALIGN=LEFT>ducators and employers alike agree that applied academics is a critical link between rigorous academics for all students and a highly trained, resourceful workforce.  AIT has been a pioneer in the tech-prep movement, providing schools with resources for the school-to-work transition that are designed to strengthen the alliance between traditional academics and vocational training.</P>

<P>Our deepening involvement in this area dates to a project undertaken in the middle 1980s.  In partnership with the Center for Occupational Research and Development, we developed an applied physics series called <I>Principles of Technology</I>.  AIT went on to develop related materials, including <I>Applied Communication</I> and a new follow-up series for high school students, called <I>Workplace Readiness</I>.</P>

<P>AIT has developed two new modules on <I>Electronic Communication</I> and <I>Technical Writing</I>, designed to help tomorrow&#146;s workers master communication skills in an increasingly technological setting.   Students are instructed in how best to send memos over electronic networks, write clear technical descriptions, and communicate with customers by voice mail, FAX, or e-mail.</P>

<P>In addition to similar curricula in other areas of applied academics, such as civics and economics, AIT has developed a multimedia series specifically designed to help students adjust to the demands of an evolving workplace.  <I>Workplace Readiness</I> teaches skills in areas such as problem solving, teamwork, and self-management.  The series was created to be used in a range of educational settings, including high school and vocational classes, associate degree programs, and career guidance and retraining courses.  Designed in cooperation with a consortium of state education agencies, <I>Workplace Readiness</I> prepares students to make a successful transition from school to a wide variety of challenging jobs.</P>

<TABLE align=right>
<TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="/profile/st_blbox.gif"><IMG SRC="/profile/micscope.jpg">
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P>AIT has also produced a professional development resource in collaboration with the University of Wisconsin&#146;s Center on Education and Work.  <I>The Road to School-to-Work: A Map for Implementation</I> provides a complete workshop package for training educators to implement and successfully maintain a school-to-career program, including sample agreement forms for businesses to initiate job shadowing and internships.</P>

<BR clear=right>
<HR>

<CENTER><TABLE cellpadding=25>
<TR><TD><FONT SIZE="+1"><I>
<IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif"><A HREF="/profile/open.htm">Opening Statement</A><BR>
<IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif"><A HREF="/profile/growth.htm">Agency Growth</A><BR>
<IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif"><A HREF="/profile/alliance.htm">Strategic Alliances</A><BR>
<IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif"><A HREF="/profile/coop_dev.htm">Cooperative Development</A>
</I></FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="+1"><I>
<IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif"><A HREF="/profile/em_tech.htm">Emerging Technologies</A><BR>
<IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif"><A HREF="/profile/prof_dev.htm">Professional Development</A><BR>
<IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif"><A HREF="/profile/technos.htm">TECHNOS Press</A><BR>
<IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif">School-to-Work Transition
</I></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

