<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>On Location: Science Links - Classroom Review Sites</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1>On Location</H1>
<H2>Science Links - Classroom Review Sites</H2>
<HR>


<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD>
<P>The development of a curriculum like <B>Science Links</B> &reg;  is a long and complex process.  It involves far more than writing a textbook and shooting an instructional video.  AIT assembles a staff nationwide to write, assemble, edit, review, and refine every aspect of the curricular resource before it is released.  Recently, an AIT production crew was on location in Pinetown, North Carolina, at one of the <B>Science Links</B> &reg;  review sites to document how the curriculum is used in class.  This video footage will be edited into a special training segment for teachers.</P></TD>
<TD WIDTH="200" ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="/images/ahead/sc_link3.gif"><BR><SMALL>&copy; 1996 Agency for Instructional Technology</SMALL></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P>AIT frequently receives feedback from teachers indicating their eagerness to introduce integrated science into their classroom.  At the same time many of these teachers have also expressed an interest in receiving training and helpful ideas.  AIT and Thomson Science are responding to this interest by providing a rich resource for teachers for each of the ten modules.</P>

<P>Using the modules in classes like the one in Pinetown, NC allows us to test the investigations.  Based upon feedback from teachers and students we refine the investigations.    Even various methods of assessment, like group presentations, are evaluated so that the curriculum can deliver a full range of options to the teacher.</P>

<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TD WIDTH="200" ALIGN=LEFT><IMG SRC="/images/ahead/sc_link4.gif"><BR><SMALL>&copy; 1996 Agency for Instructional Technology</SMALL></TD>
<TD><P>If you are interested in your classroom serving as a <B>Science Links</B> &reg;  review site contact Brad Bloom, Assistant Producer at <A HREF="MAILTO:bbloom@ait.net">bbloom@ait.net</A> or call 800-457-4509 ext. 210.  If you are interested in being a review site for other curriculums please indicate what subject areas and grade levels you teach.</P>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P><B>Science Links</B> &reg;  offers a wide selection of investigations for your class.  Practical to use with minimal lab resources, the investigations are designed to meet the new National Science Education Standards AND make learning interesting.  <A HREF="/ahead/investigation.htm">To try a sample investigation from <B>Science Links</B> &reg;  click here.</P></A>


<HR>

