<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Look Ahead - Before the Bell Rings: What Every Paraeducator Should Know</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1>Before the Bell Rings:</H1>
<H2>What Every Paraeducator Should Know</H2>
<HR>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Staff Development</H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
One 60-minute video for teachers, administrators, and paraeducators</P>
<HR>

<IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/bell1.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>
<H3>The need for paraeducators is growing by leaps and bounds all over America.</H3>

<P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT><B><I>Before the Bell Rings</I></B> is a detailed guide explaining what a paraeducator does, their role with teachers, responsibilities and regulations, and the vital role that teacher's assistants play in today's highly interactive classroom.</P>

<P>In clear, concise language, <B><I>Before the Bell Rings</I></B> demonstrates every aspect of the teacher/paraeducator relationship with actual classroom examples, workshop handouts, and discussions with experienced  "veterans" in this demanding profession.  The wide range of roles that paraeducators are called on to perform in today's educational services have created a host of special issues for teachers, administrators, paraeducators, and parents:
<UL>
<LI>When do the roles of paraeducators and teachers overlap?
<LI>What are the most important ethical considerations for paraeducators?
<LI>How is an effective team built?
<LI>What skills and techniques in behavior management must the paraeducator develop?
<LI>How best can we refine our problem-solving and communication skills?
</UL></P>

<P><B><I>Before the Bell Rings</I></B> is a sixty-minute video produced by AIT that includes a comprehensive facilitators guide and 11 Handout/Transparencies for workshop use. &copy; 1995 AIT</P>

<HR WIDTH="50%">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><I>Before the Bell Rings</I></H2>

<P>Created by Anna Lou Pickett and Patty Lee, <B><I>Before the Bell Rings</I></B> addresses every aspect of the professional paraeducator field.  Far more than teacher's aides or assistants, today's paraeducator may be involved in all facets of education, from special education to health services to support functions and classroom instruction for the "at-risk" student.</P>

<H2>Program Segments</H2>
<P><B>Part I, <I>Building a Team,</I></B> delineates the similarities and differences between a teacher and a paraeducator and provides advice on how to build a spirit of effective teamwork.</P>

<P><B>Part II, <I>Roles and Responsibilities,</I></B> further explores the teacher/paraeducator relationship examines where there are overlaps, and what duties are solely those of the teacher or paraeducator.</P>

<P><B>Part III, <I>Professional and Ethical Responsibilities,</I></B> focuses on ethical considerations:
<UL>
<LI>maintaining confidentiality
<LI>protecting students' right to due process, dignity, privacy, and respect
<LI>the need for honesty, loyalty, dependability, and accountability
<LI>adopting a cooperative spirit and a willingness to learn.
</UL></P>

<P><B>Part IV, <I>Communication and Problem Solving,</I></B> presents several scenarios involving the need for communication and problem-solving skills and promotes discussion of alternatives for resolving conflict.</P>

<P><B>Part V, <I>Behavior Management,</I></B> stresses the importance of effective, but respectful, techniques of managing at-risk, impaired, or emotionally disturbed children.  Disruptive behavior is challenging and this segment offers proven advice on developing a strategy to deal with it.</P>

<P><B>Part VI, <I>Conclusion,</I></B> provides a review of the informaiton presented throughout the workshop and strategies for teaching and maintaining psoitive behavior.</P>

<HR WIDTH="50%">

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>A comprehensive, in-depth guide to the evolving<BR>world of the professional paraeducator.</H3>

<P><B><I>Before the Bell Rings</I></B> addresses virtually every aspect of this growing professional field&#151;how to build an effective team, the relationship and roles of teachers and paraeducators, ethical issues, managing behavior problems and the needs of special-care students, and how to develop the most efficient communication and problem-solving skills.  Together, the video and facilitators guide can be used to create a highly effective workshop for teachers, administrators, parents, and paraeducators.</P>

<P>Clear classroom examples and advice from successful "veterans" in the paraeducator field, <B><I>Before the Bell Rings</I></B> is required viewing (and reading!) for everyone involved in today's demanding educational system.</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/bell2.gif"><BR><B><I>We all need to do our homework</I>&#151;Before the Bell Rings!</B></P>

<HR>

