<HEAD>
<TITLE>Video Adventures of Lost and Found</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1>Video Adventures of Lost and Found</H1>
<HR>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Preschool</H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Three early-learning skills programs for preschool students</P>
<HR>

<IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/lost1.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>
<H3>The adventures of Lost and Found!</H3>

<P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT>Lost is an at-wits-end bumbler; Found is his scientist friend.  Together with their many other friends, they use songs and demonstrations to solve mysteries and teach important life skills. Loads of action present preschoolers with an exciting world of play and learning.  Lost and Found provide stimulating role models who teach safety and new words and sounds.  Children pattern their behavior on figures who are fun and imaginative.</P>
<UL>
<LI>Preschoolers will learn to identify dangers and risks.
<LI>They will learn sounds and words from the zoo, farm, and fire station.
<LI>Lively songs reinforce each concept throughout the action-paced videos.
</UL>

<IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/lost2.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>
<P><B><I>Video Adventures of Lost and Found</I></B> is a series of three 20-28 minute tapes and an accompanying teacher's guide with tips for extended activities.  It is produced by Attainment Company Production and distributed by AIT. &copy; 1996</P>

<HR WIDTH="50%">

<H2><I>Video Adventures of Lost and Found</I></H2>

<P>The preschool years are the active years&#151;and learning from action-packed videos encourages youngsters to model their behavior on characters that they find captivating.   Follow Lost and Found as they search for the missing twins, the missing sounds, and sing upbeat, silly songs.</P>

<H2>Programs</H2>
<OL>
<LI><P><B>Stay Safe!</B><BR>
Follow Lost and Found as they begin their action adventure on a madcap search for the missing twins. The adventure soon becomes a fast-paced exploration of essential safety skills. Watch Out Willie helps Lost and Found learn to be aware of hot stoves, strangers, electrical outlets, traffic dangers, and many other safety topics.</P>

<LI><P><B>Stolen Sounds</B><BR>
Twang, Lost and Found's space pal, has been taking pictures of the animals with his special camera&#151;and now the animals have lost their sounds!  It is a mystery that they must solve and along the way, we visit a zoo, a farm, and a fire station.  We learn new words every step of the way and learn to associate sounds with their sources.</P>

<LI><P><B>Learning Tunes</B><BR>
Action! Fun! Singing! Each song from this wacky collection of original tunes from the <B>Stay Safe!</B> and <B>Stolen Sounds</B> videos is a lesson and a learning experience.</P>
</OL>

<HR WIDTH="50%">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Sing along with Lost and Found</H2>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Lost and Found (theme)</H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
We're Lost and Found<BR>
The Greatest Shop Around!<BR>
Hello! Welcome!<BR>
How are you today?<BR>
Would you like to stay? OK!<BR>
Twang!<BR>
Hello! I'm lost!<BR>
I know my way around!<BR>
Hello! Welcome!<BR>
You can call me Found!</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/lost3.gif"></P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Words and Sounds</H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Words and sounds<BR>
Are everywhere you look<BR>
Around your house<BR>
And inside every book<BR>
For everything<BR>
There is a word and sound<BR>
All you have to do<BR>
Is look around</P>

