<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Look Ahead - The New Legacy</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1>The New Legacy</H1>
<HR>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Social Studies</H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Ten 15-minute programs for high school students</P>
<HR>

<IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/legacy1.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>
<H3>Updated, new version of the award-winning series <I>American Legacy.</I></H3>

<P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT>The original series, <B><I>American Legacy</I></B>, was a geographic and topical exploration of life in America&#151;its diversity, resources, political divisions, and natural features.  It has been one of the most successful series of its kind and now, a generation later, many changes have occurred.</P>

<P><B><I>The New Legacy</I></B> is an extraordinary teaching resource.  Together, the combination of the stunning scenes and narration from the video, the in-depth problem-solving activities of the CD-ROM, the extended activities and topics suggested in the teacher's guide, and the resource materials and discussion group format of the on-line Web service create a powerful classroom tool.  These elements provide students and teachers with an opportunity to explore America like never before.  America's geographic, cultural, and economic diversity is at the heart of what makes our country what it is and how we have evolved over time.</P>

<P>Rich in content, culturally sensitive, and instructionally versatile, <B><I>The New Legacy</I></B> emphasizes the concept of the interdependence of each region of the United States, as well as the qualities that make each region distinctive.</P>

<P>This series will be available as a pre-production lease.  All agencies who join the PPL will receive four years use for three years lease fee.  At renewal time, members qualify for a 25% discount and can buy the teacher's guide for the lowest discounted price.</P>

<P><B><I>The New Legacy</I></B> includes a series of ten 15-minute programs, a teacher's guide, an available on-line Web service, and a CD-ROM.  It is being produced by station KRMA-TV, Denver, and distributed by AIT. &copy; 1997</P>

<HR WIDTH="50%">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><I>The New Legacy</I></H2>

<IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/legacy2.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>
<H2>Programs<BR>
<SMALL>(working titles and concepts)</SMALL></H2>

<P><B><I>The New Legacy</I></B> explores the wide sweep of America's past and present.  Programs will examine the issues that have shaped our historic, cultural, and economic development.  Topics covered in the new series include:</P>
<OL><B>
<LI>Megalopolis, the East
<LI>The Southeast
<LI>The New Look of the Old South
<LI>The Industrial Midwest
<LI>The World's Breadbasket
<LI>Ranch Country
<LI>The Rockies
<LI>Alaska: The Last Wilderness
<LI>Gateway to the Pacific Rim
<LI>Megalopolis, the West
</B></OL>

<H2>CD-ROM</H2>

<P>The CD-ROM uses a problem-solving approach and research focus to address issues of national importance:</P>
<UL>
<LI>Should water from the Rockies be diverted to support a desert community?
<LI>Should federal dollars be used to build a mass-transit system in Los Angeles?
<LI>Should the U.S. government ban grain sales to a nation that supports terrorism?
<LI>Should tobacco products be banned, licensed, or subsidized?
</UL>

<P>Using the research information available on the CD-ROM and the on-line Web service, students become engrossed in the process as they are asked to act as advisors to the "president."   They must access data, develop informed opinions, and prepare reports on how best to deal with these and many other issues.</P>

<HR WIDTH="50%">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Updated, new version of the award-<BR>winning series <I>American Legacy.</I></H2>

<P>Four key elements make up the exhilarating investigation of the American land and life that is <B><I>The New Legacy.</I></B></P>
<UL>
<LI><P>Follow us on a train journey hosted by young, enthusiastic narrators who take us through each region of the U.S. with the help of breathtaking video and film footage and strong graphics.</P>
<LI><P>A CD-ROM multimedia program that presents students the challenge of acting as advisors to the "president" on a wide range of topical issues.</P>
<LI><P>A Teacher's Guide provides extended discussion topics and activities based on the video, and a guide to using the resources available on the CD-ROM and on-line service that can be used as an exciting research tool.</P>
<LI><P>An on-line service for further exploration and dialogue with other teachers and/or students on the issues presented, as well as resource materials where students may find data and answers to help them investigate the problems and issues presented.</P>
</UL>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/legacy3.gif"><BR>
Our history is present in our today&#151;and that is the new legacy.</P>

<HR>

