<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Look Ahead - Timothy Traddle</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1>Timothy Traddle</H1>
<HR>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Social Studies</H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Twenty-four 5-minute programs on problem solving for preschool sudents</P>
<HR>


<IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/traddle.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE="20" VSPACE="10">
<H3>26 of the "funnest" puzzles ever for preschoolers!</H3>
<P>Timothy Traddle is a big, green turtle&#151;and a singing, dancing detective! Every five-minute segment in the Timothy Traddle adventure series deals with a problem that needs to be solved.  He has only blue and yellow paint, how can he paint a green tree?  His soccer ball is stuck in a tree&#151;how to get it down?</P>

<TABLE WIDTH="100%" CELLPADDING="6">
<TR><TD WIDTH="50%" VALIGN="TOP">
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Programs</H2>
<OL>
<B><LI>Timothy Wants a Skateboard</B> (5:08)
<B><LI>Blue and Yellow Make Green</B> (5:04)
<B><LI>Skipping Rope</B> (5:06)
<B><LI>Ball in the Tree</B> (4:09)
<B><LI>Two Kites</B> (4:52)
<B><LI>Sandpit</B> (4:59)
<B><LI>Paintings</B> (4:52)
<B><LI>A Hole in a Beach Ball</B> (5:14)
<B><LI>Gift Wrap Paper</B> (4:57)
<B><LI>Beads</B> (5:12)
<B><LI>Newspaper and Paint</B> (5:35)
<B><LI>Washing Line</B> (5:03)
<B><LI>See-saw</B> (4:37)
<B><LI>A Plant Needs Roots to Grow</B> (5:02)
<B><LI>Wind and Drawings</B> (5:10)
<B><LI>The Racquet</B> (4:59)
<B><LI>Mending a Toy</B> (4:43)
<B><LI>A Tulip for Sally</B> (5:21)
<B><LI>What Soaks up Water</B> (4:55)
<B><LI>A Covered Wound Heals Quicker</B> (4:56)
<B><LI>Make Work Easier</B> (5:14)
<B><LI>Sending a Letter</B> (5:09)
<B><LI>Using a Heavy Objec</B>t (4:56)
<B><LI>Lifting a Heavy Object</B> (5:07)
</OL>

</TD><TD WIDTH="50%">
<P>Timothy has a lot of friends and he is in love with the whole, big, wide world.  His friends always stop by just in the nick of time and every solution is a practical learning experience that preschoolers will never forget.  Timothy has a puzzle song that gets them up and dancing along&#151;a turtle with a talent for teaching.</P>

<P><B>Timothy Traddle</B> is a series of twenty-four 5-minute programs with accompanying teachers guide containing descriptions of each segment and suggestions for extended activities for each of the lessons.  It is distributed by AIT (Agency for Instructional Technology) and was produced by the South African Broadcasting Company (SABC). &copy; 1997 by AIT.</P>
<HR WIDTH="50%">

<P ALIGN=CENTER><BIG>For more information, contact:</BIG></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" BORDER=0></A></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>Broadcast Sales & Marketing<BR>
800/236-6248 or<BR>
812/339-2203, ext. 236<BR>
FAX 812/333-4218</B><BR>
Box A, Bloomington, IN 47402-0120</P>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

