<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Look Ahead - Village of Kindness</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1>Village of Kindness</H1>
<HR>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Staff Development</H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
Ten 30-minute programs for child care providers, early childhood educators, and parents</P>
<HR>

<IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/village1.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>
<H3>A complete guide for the in-home child-care provider.</H3>

<P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT><B><I>Village of Kindness</I></B> is bursting with literally hundreds of tips for the in-home child-care provider.  There are detailed instructions on every aspect of providing high-quality care, from how to organize your care on a sound business footing to giving special care to the impaired or injured child.  From infants to kindergarten-age, this highly practical guide is invaluable advice for all&#151;experienced and newcomer alike.</P>

<P><B><I>Village of Kindness</I></B> addresses the everyday needs and myriad problems of the care-giver with sensitivity, insight, and fun-to-watch video examples.  Care-givers will learn to:</P>
<UL>
<LI>Seek out the local experts and ask the right questions.
<LI>Write contracts and interact with parents effectively.
<LI>Create a stimulating and friendly environment for children.
<LI>Understand the importance of health, safety, and nutrition.
<LI>Identify and care for special-needs children, and when to recommend professional evaluation and assistance.
<LI>Direct play and begin to help children enjoy the learning process.
</UL>

<P><B><I>Village of Kindness</I></B> is a ten-part series with accompanying user's manual produced by the Board of Regents of the University of Wisconsin System and includes a guide to additional resources and reference materials for the in-home child-care provider. &copy; 1995</P>

<HR WIDTH=50%">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><I>Village of Kindness</I></H2>

<P><B><I>Village of Kindness</I></B> takes us through the process of establishing an in-home child-care facility in a comprehensive, step-by-step instruction.  The video and accompanying manual deal with every aspect of this most caring of the arts.  Advice and anecdotes from many experienced "veterans" help to make the guide accessible, yet authoritative.</P>

<H2>Programs</H2>
<OL>
<LI><P><B>Right from the Start: Taking you First Steps in Family Child Care</B><BR>
<I>Right from the Start</I> gets you off on the right foot&#151;how do you find out what you need to know about contracts, regulations, and what you need to offer. (28:25)</P>

<LI><P><B>The Heart of the Matter: Building Relationships for Hich Quality Family Child Care</B><BR>
<I>The Heart of the Matter</I> takes you through the process of evaluating yourself as a care-giver, and building relationships with parents. (28:40)</P>

<LI><P><B>There's No Place Like Home: Preparing Your Evironment for Family Child Care</B><BR>
<I>There's No Place Like Home</I> covers all aspects of creating a safe and stimulating environment for children. (27:52)</P>

<LI><P><B>Play It Safe: Assuring Health, Safety and Nutrition in Your Home</B><BR>
<I>Play It Safe</I> provides detailed advice on promoting physical and emotional health in your home-care environment. (28:18)</P>

<LI><P><B>First Steps: Provideing High Quality Care for Infants and Toddlers</B><BR>
<I>First Steps</I> addresses the special needs of infants and toddlers, from diapering to the "terrible two's." (28:16)</P>

<LI><P><B>Through Children's Eyes: Providing Appropriate Care for Preschool and School-Age Children</B><BR>
<I>Through Children's Eyes</I> covers preschoolers&#151;the  physical, talkative, learning to interact, and playful stage. (28:27)</P>

<LI><P><B>Play for Keeps: Planning the Curriculum in Family Child Care</B><BR>
<I>Play for Keeps</I> details the wonderful world of play and learning. (28:14)</P>

<LI><P><B>All For One and One For All:  Providing Inclusive Child Care in Your Home</B><BR>
<I>All For One and One For All</I> shows you how to deal with the impaired or disabled in family day care. (28:42)</P>

<LI><P><B>Teachable Moments: Developing Effective Teaching Strategies</B><BR>
<I>Teachable Moments</I> summarizes your role as the transition from day-care to school; guiding children and instilling the love of learning. (28:21)</P>

<LI><P><B>A Business of Trust:  Becoming a Professional Family Child Care Provider</B><BR>
<I>A Business of Trust</I> provides detailed advice on the various aspects of becoming a professional child-care provider, including tax advice! (27:52)</P>
</OL>

<HR WIDTH="50%">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Detailed, step-by-step guide for all child-care providers; insightful and caring!</H2>

<P>Day-care providers now have a complete guide to in-home care.  <B><I>Village of Kindness</I></B>  covers every aspect of this essential service, from toddlers to taxes, safety to self-esteem, diapers to care for the disabled.</P>

<P><B><I>Village of Kindness</I></B>  is a 10-part video series and comprehensive accompanying manual that deals with child-care from A to Z.  The warm tone of the video brings you right into the world of in-home care, with thoughtful tips from dozens of working professionals who are generous with their experience.</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/ahead/first/village2.gif"><BR><B><I>"It takes a village to raise a child!"</I></B></P>

<HR>

