<HEAD>
<TITLE>Workplace Readiness - Problem Solving Program</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><A NAME="TOP"><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></A></TD><TD>

<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1>Workplace Readiness</H1>
<HR>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Problem Solving Unit</H1>

<P>Improve employee problem-solving skills for responding to changes in the workplace. Introduce a five-step process for solving problems effectively: Defining the Situation, Stating the Goal, Identifying a Solution, Preparing a Plan, and Taking Action.</P>

<P>Prepare learners to apply this process to workplace situations and improve their ability to solve problems independently and in groups (Each module contains five lessons that focus on one step in the process.</P>

<IMG SRC="/images/pictures/317problem.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>
<P ALIGN=RIGHT>Module 2: <I>Stating the Goal</I> focuses on how paramedics<BR> at Grady Memorial Hospital EMS state goals.</P>

<H2><BR CLEAR=RIGHT>Modules:</H2>
<OL>
<B><LI>The Changing Workplace</B>
<P>See how employers are using employees&#146; problem-solving skills to respond to workplace changes.  Study examples of how effective problem solving enables employers to compete successfully in the global marketplace.</P>

<B><LI>Defining the Situation</B>
<P>Prepare learners to recognize problems in the workplace.  Practice defining problem situations by systematically asking questions and gathering and evaluating information.</P>

<B><LI>Stating the Goal</B>
<P>Learn how to generate and evaluate goals.</P>

<B><LI>Identifying a Solution</B>
<P>Examine how to develop a variety of potential solutions vegore choosing the one that will best help solve a problem.</P>

<B><LI>Preparing a Plan</B>
<P>Practice preparing and finalizing a detailed plan.</P>

<B><LI>Taking Action</B>
<P>Illustrate how to monitor the plan, check results, and review the process once an plan is implemented.</P>
</OL>

<HR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><BIG>Return to AIT&#146;s <A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c317.htm">Workplace Readiness</A> product description page.</BIG></P>

<P><A HREF="/ait/aitcopy.htm">&copy; AIT</A></P>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
