<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Workplace Readiness - Teamwork Unit</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><A NAME="TOP"><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></A></TD><TD>

<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1>Workplace Readiness</H1>
<HR>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Teamwork Solving Unit</H1>

<P>Identify the factors and develop the skills necessary for becoming part of a successful team&#151;clear goals, trust, and support for each other.</P>

<P>Practice these skills for building and maintaining teams that communicate effectively, share leadership responsibilities, and work together to resolve conflict utilizing a &#147;win-win&#148; approach.</P>

<IMG SRC="/images/pictures/317teamwork.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>
<P ALIGN=RIGHT><BR>In Module 4: <I>Diversity in the Work Force</I> the employees at the Scottsdale Plaza Resort in Scottsdale, Arizona show how team members overcome ethnic barriers to achieve full team participation.</P>

<H2><BR CLEAR=RIGHT>Modules:</H2>
<OL>
<B><LI>The Changing Workplace</B>
<P>Study companies that are responding to workplace changes by using teams to meet new challenges.  Analyze skills that make teams effective.</P>

<B><LI>What is an Effective Team?</B>
<P>Investigate how team effectiveness skills are related to task and process functions.  Learn why teams operate best in a climate of mutual trust and why members must be prepared to share in the team&#146;s leadership.</P>

<B><LI>Shared Leadership</B>
<P>Demonstrate how sharing leadership means performing task and process functions Teach learners to distinguish between behaviors that make team functions difficult and those that make team functions easier.</P>

<B><LI>Diversity</B>
<P>Meet real employees who communicate, solve problems, work to produce quality goods and services, and discuss working in teams.  Develop learner&#146;s skills for becoming effective team members.</P>

<B><LI>Conflict Resolution</B>
<P>Study a model for resolving conflicts.  Practice this model, using several short video clips about workplace conflicts as triggers.  Illustrate why the best way to resolve a conflict is with a &#147;win-win&#148; approach that benefits everyone involved.</P>
</OL>

<HR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><BIG>Return to AIT&#146;s <A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c317.htm">Workplace Readiness</A> product description page.</BIG></P>

<P><A HREF="/ait/aitcopy.htm">&copy; AIT</A></P>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
