<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Workplace Readiness - Self-Management Unit</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><A NAME="TOP"><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></A></TD><TD>

<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1>Workplace Readiness</H1>
<HR>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Self Management Unit</H1>

<P>Build the skills necessary to take responsibility and adjust to the changing demands of the workplace.  Apply a three-step approach to managing personal job performance and career transitions.  Prepare learners to use this approach for adapting to new technologies or processes, upgrading skills, and career planning.</P>

<P>Examine the importance of students taking responsibility for their own success, on the job and in future careers.  Illustrate the effects of attendance, punctuality, safety procedures, quality workmanship, and drug and alcohol abuse prevention to job performance.</P>


<IMG SRC="/images/pictures/317self.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>
<P ALIGN=RIGHT><BR>In Module 2: <I>Personal Performance</I> Joey, an employee of Cushman, demonstrates the need for self-management, as indicated by his performance report.</P>

<H2><BR CLEAR=RIGHT>Modules:</H2>
<OL>
<B><LI>The Changing Workplace</B>
<P>Examine how two companies respond to changing consumer demand, rapid innovation, and heightened domestic and international competition in the marketplace.</P>

<B><LI>Personal Performance</B>
<P>Develop the skills needed to meet company performance standards.  Analyze examples of what may happen when performance standards are not met, and practice a simple problem-solving approach to improve job performance.</P>

<B><LI>Personal Transitions</B>
<P>Explore how frequent changes in today&#146;s workplace&#151;new techniques, upskilling of jobs, restructuring of organizations, job obsolescence&#151;have a serious impact on a worker&#146;s career.  Prepare learners to respond positively to change by viewing it as an opportunity for growth and by accepting responsibility for their own job transitions.</P>
</OL>

<HR>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><BIG>Return to AIT&#146;s <A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c317.htm">Workplace Readiness</A> product description page.</BIG></P>

<P><A HREF="/ait/aitcopy.htm">&copy; AIT</A></P>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
