<TITLE>AIT.Net News, Fall 1995 - A perfect fit: Workplace Readiness develops SCANS skills</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<A HREF="/technos/atechnos.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/technos/tpress.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>AIT.Net News, Fall 1995</H1>
<HR>

<H2>A perfect fit</H2>

<H3><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c317.htm"><B>Workplace Readiness</B></A> develops SCANS Skills</H3>

<P>Where would a resource that covers problem solving, teamwork, and self-management skills fit in your curriculum? And why should you consider sharing it with your students? The answers are simple. AIT's <A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c317.htm"> <B>Workplace Readiness</B></A> can complement nearly any course because its emphasis is on preparing today's learners for tomorrow's workplace.</P>

<P>When you integrate "Workplace Readiness" into your curriculum, you will help your students master the five competences that lie at the heart of successful job performance, regardless of the knowledge required: the effective use of resources, interpersonal skills, information, systems, and technology.</P>

<P>These competencies were identified by the Secretary's Commission on Achieving Necessary Skills (SCANS) in "What Work Requires of Schools: A SCANS Report for America 2000" and formed the basis for "Workplace Readiness." The following chart correlates the materials presented in "Workplace Readiness" to the five competencies recommended by the SCANS report.</P>

<TABLE BORDER>
<TR><TD><B>SCANS Competencies</B><BR>
<SMALL>Effective workers can productively use:</SMALL></TD>
<TD COLSPAN=2><B>"Workplace Readiness" Materials</B></TD></TR>

<TR><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD>RESOURCES</TD><TD>UNIT</TD><TD>MODULE</TD></TR>

<TR><TD ROWSPAN=2>time</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>2-6</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Self-Management</TD><TD>2, 3</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>money</TD><TD>--</TD><TD>--</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>material and facilities</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>2-6</TD></TR>

<TR><TD ROWSPAN=2>human resources</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>2-6</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Self-Management</TD><TD>2, 3</TD></TR>

<TR><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD>INTERPERSONAL SKILLS</TD><TD>UNIT</TD><TD> MODULE</TD></TR>

<TR><TD ROWSPAN=2>participating as member of a team</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>2-6</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Teamwork</TD><TD>2, 3</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>teaching others new skills</TD><TD>--</TD><TD>--</TD></TR>

<TR><TD ROWSPAN=2>serving clients and customers</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>6</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Teamwork</TD><TD>2, 3</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>exercising leadership</TD><TD>Teamwork</TD><TD>3</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>negotiating</TD><TD>Teamwork</TD><TD>5</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>working with diversity</TD><TD>Teamwork</TD><TD>4</TD></TR>

<TR><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD>INFORMATION</TD><TD>UNIT</TD><TD> MODULE</TD></TR>

<TR><TD ROWSPAN=2>acquiring and evaluating information</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>all modules</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Self-Management</TD><TD>all modules</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>organizing and maintaining information</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>2-4</TD></TR>

<TR><TD ROWSPAN=2>interpreting and communicating information</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>2-5</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Teamwork</TD><TD>2-4</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>using computers to process information</TD><TD>--</TD><TD>--</TD></TR>

<TR><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD>SYSTEMS</TD><TD>UNIT</TD><TD> MODULE</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>understanding systems</TD><TD>All units</TD><TD>"Changing Workplace" modules</TD></TR>

<TR><TD ROWsPAN=2>monitoring and correcting performance</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>2-6</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Self-Management</TD><TD>2, 3</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>improving or designing systems</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>5, 6</TD></TR>

<TR><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD>TECHNOLOGY</TD><TD>UNIT</TD><TD> MODULE</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>selecting technology</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>2-6</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>applying technology to tasks</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>2-6</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>maintaining and troubleshooting equipment</TD><TD>Problem Solving</TD><TD>2-5</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<P>When you consider resources for your students, you probably also consider how the materials measure up. Will the course help your students develop the skills they need? Does it meet the competencies established by experts in the field? "AIT.Net News" provides this vital piece of the puzzle by including correlations for selected AIT resources.</P>

<P>Skills correlation charts are available by calling AIT Customer Service at (800) 457-4509, ext. 279.</P>

