<P><B>IN</B>PERSON</P>
<H2>Mark your calendar</H2>
<H3>And plan on meeting us in person</H3>

<P>AIT representatives will be attending the meetings marked with an asterisk (*). Booth numbers and locations have been provided where known.</P>

<P><B>JANUARY</B></P>
<P><B>30-31*</B>. The Careers Conference, <A HREF="http://www.cew.wisc.edu"><B>Center on Education and Work</B></A>, Madison, WI. Contact: (608) 262-9264.</P>

<P><B>FEBRUARY</B></P>
<P><B>7-9*</B>. NCTM Regional, Rapid City, SD. Contact: (703) 620-9840.</P>

<P><B>15-17*</B>. Association for Educational and Communications Technology (AECT) INCITE, Indianapolis, IN. Contact: (202) 347-7834.  Booth No. 326.</P>

<P><B>MARCH</B></P>

<P><B>2-6</B>. <A HREF="http://www.spa.org"><B>Software Publishers Association</B></A>'s 1996 Spring Symposium, San Francisco, CA. Contact: Loni Singer at (202) 452-1600, Ext. 353, or lsinger@spa.org.</P>

<P><B>16-19*</B>. <A HREF="http://www.ascd.org"><B>Association for Supervision and Curriculum Development</B></A> 1996 Conference and Exhibit Show, New Orleans, LA. Contact: (703) 549-9110.  Booth No. 255.</P>

<HR>

<H3>Educational Science Leadership Institutes</H3>

<H4>Application Deadline: March 1, 1996</H4>

<P>For the eighth year, the National Science Resources Center (NSRC) will be conducting two Elementary Science Leadership Institutes at the Smithsonian Institution in Washington, D.C., during the weeks of June 23-28, 1996, and July 21-26, 1996. Up to 20 teams of four to eight participants are accepted at each institute.</P>

<P>Teams represent local school districts and are comprised of school district administrators, teachers, and scientists. Through the NSRC Leadership Institutes, these people become more effective resources and catalysts for improving elementary science education within their communities.</P>

<P>For information or application materials, contact Director of Outreach, NSRC, 600 Maryland Avenue S.W., Suite 880, Washington, D.C. 20024, (202) 287-2063, fax (202) 287-2070, jlee@nas.edu.</P>

