<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>TECHNOS Press - Conference Proceedings</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>

<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<A HREF="/technos/atechnos.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/technos/tpress.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>TECHNOS Press</H1>
<HR>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>TECHNOS Press &#151; What&#146;s Fair</H2>
<H3 ALIGN=RIGHT>A Report on the Proceeding of the National Conference on Educational Fair Access and the New Media</H3>
<HR>

<H3>Contents</H3>
<P>
<B>INTRODUCTION</B><BR>
by <A HREF="/technos/proceed/MSullivan.htm">Michael F. Sullivan</A></P>
<P>
<B>KEYNOTE ADDRESSES</B><BR>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/RWedgeworth.htm">A New Framework for Educational Uses of Copyrighted Works</A><BR>
by Robert Wedgeworth</P>
<P>
Multimedia Patent and Copyright Issues:  The Need for Lawmakers to Be Multimedia Literate<BR>
by Fred Hofstetter</P>
<P>
<B>PRESENTATIONS</B><BR>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/BRinger.htm">Register of Copyright Perspective</A><BR>
by Barbara Ringer</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/BLehman.htm">Department of Commerce and Patent and Trademark Office Perspective</A><BR>
by Bruce A. Lehman</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/MRibaudo.htm">Copyright Issues from the Perspective of an Academic Administrator</A><BR>
by Michael Ribaudo</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/JBaumgarten.htm">Corporate Perspective</A><BR>
by Jon A. Baumgarten</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/BMullin.htm">Getting Your Music's Worth Beyond Fair Use</A><BR>
by Bill Mullin</P>
<P>
Guidelines for Multimedia Productions: A Copyright Owner's View<BR>
by Bernard R. Sorkin</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/CBenton.htm">Association for Information Media and Equipment Perspective</A><BR>
by Charles Benton</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/RHeterick.htm">Managing Intellectual Property on the Net</A><BR>
by Robert C. Heterick, Jr.</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/CRisher.htm">Use of Copyrighted Works in Multimedia: A Publisher's Perspective</A><BR>
by Carol A. Risher</P>
<P>
Copyright Law Providing Access to Information<BR>
Charles Schneebeck</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/HBotterbusch.htm">Position Statement of the Association for Educational Communications and Technology</A><BR>
by Hope Roland Botterbusch</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/MMosley.htm">Multimedia Development and Copyright Issues in the Maricopa Community Colleges</A><BR>
by Mary Lou Mosley</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/KHowat.htm">New Media Centers Program: Forum for Research and Development of Multimedia Technologies in Education</A><BR>
by Kevin J. Howat</P>
<P>
During the National Conference on Educational Fair Access and the New Media, participants met in small sessions where working committees discussed possible guidelines governing three difficult copyright issues that particularly affect the handling of new electronic and digitized media: the quantity and sources of excerpted materials; the presentation, utilization, and duplication of copyrighted materials; and the retention, access, and storage of multimedia materials. On the final morning, participants met in general session to hear committee reports. A summary of each report follows.</P>
<P>
<B>REPORTS OF THE WORKING COMMITTEES</B><BR>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/JSichel.htm">Committee on the Quantity and Sources of Excerpted Materials</A><BR>
by Jan Sichel</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/LLivingston.htm">Committee on the Presentation, Utilization, and Duplication of Copyrighted Materials</A><BR>
by Lisa Livingston</P>
<P>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/CRace.htm">Committee on the Retention, Access, and Storage of Multimedia Materials</A><BR>
by Carol A. Race</P>
<P>
<B>GENERAL DISCUSSION, JUNE 17, 1994</B><BR>
<A HREF="/technos/proceed/IBender.htm">Ivan R. Bender, Chairperson</A></P>
<P>
<B>APPENDICES</B><BR>
