<h1 ALIGN=CENTER>Virginia Bacheler</h1>

<BLOCKQUOTE>I started out voicing the <b>"THIS WEEK IN WORLD HISTORIES"</b> on <b>Assignment:  The World </b>some 19 years ago.  When <b>WXXI</b> asked me if I'd like to host the show, I jumped at the chance.  That was 18 years ago.  I began my broadcasting career in college, working at the college radio station at William Smith College in Geneva, New York.  After receiving my masters in television from the S. I. Newhouse School at Syracuse University, I worked in commercial television as a reporter/producer.  I'm now an associate professor at SUNY Brockport teaching braodcast journalism and writing.  I'm married to Skip Battaglia, a film animator, and have one daughter.  We share our house with one very bossy cat.  In my spare time I like to read, bake and practice aerobic gardening.</BLOCKQUOTE>

