<HTML>
<TITLE>Before the Bell Rings #385</TITLE>
<BODY>

<H2>Before the Bell Rings:  What Every PARAEDUCATOR Should Know</H2>

Professional Development, Paraeducator Training, and Teaching Techniques for Preservice/Inservice Educators<P>

Develop education's most vital untapped resource--the paraeducator. <B>Before the Bell Rings: What Every Paraeducator Should Know</B> is a video and print workshop resource that will enable you to prepare your education team to implement ongoing professional development programs for paraeducators in preschool, elementary, and secondary education.  Train paraeducators to communicate more effectively with teachers, administrators, parents, and students. Define the roles and responsibilities of paraeducators, especially in relation to the education team. Develop paraeducators' problem solving and behavior management techniques, and prepare them to actively practice your district's professional and ethical standards of conduct.<P>

Paraeducators are helping schools meet new educational challenges, like inclusion, multiculturalism, teaching ESL students, and working with children from family backgrounds that place them at risk. To meet the needs of today's larger, more diverse student populations, schools are looking to highly skilled paraeducators for answers. Paraeducators are also important members in Title I and IDEA (Individuals with Disabilities Education Act) programs. In fact, it is estimated that nearly 500,000 Title I-funded staff positions are filled by paraeducators. Funding for professional development opportunities for paraeducators is also called for under Title II (The Dwight D. Eisenhower Professional Development Program) guidelines.<P>

<B>Video Program</B><BR>
Anna Lou Pickett, the leading authority on paraeducator training, provides insights into the importance of developing a skilled paraeducator workforce. Paraeducators, teachers, and administrators from schools across the United States offer examples and proven strategies for building a successful paraeducator program in your school or district.  The video program is divided into six parts, each organized around one phase of paraeducator training and development:
<UL TYPE=DISC>
<LI>Building a Team
<LI>Roles and Responsibilities
<LI>Professional and Ethical Responsibilities
<LI>Communication and Problem Solving
<LI>Behavior Management
<LI>Conclusion
</UL><P>

<B>Facilitator's Guide</B><BR>
The facilitator's guide contains professional development activities and follow-up materials for two workshop formats. The guide includes detailed workshop agendas, program previews and objectives, role-play scenarios, reproducible handout masters, overhead masters, follow-up activities to each part of the video program, and listings of additional resources.<P>

Before the Bell Rings was produced by Video Features, Inc. and AIT (1996).<P>

<H3>Purchase</H3>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD>The Complete Set</TD><TD>(#385-M01)</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>$295.00</TD></TR>
