<HEAD>
<TITLE>AIT Board of Directors - William L. Lepley</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1>AIT Board of Directors</H1>
<HR>

<P><IMG SRC="lepley.jpg" ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE="10" RIGHT HSPACE="10">
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><BR><I>William L. Lepley</I></H2>
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>President<BR>
<A HREF="HTTP://www.hershey.pvt.k12.pa.us">Milton Hershey School</A></H3>
<HR></P>

<P>William L. Lepley has been the President and Chief Executive Officer of Milton Hershey School since September 1993. He is also a member of the Executive Committee of the Board of Directors of the Hershey Trust Company and the M. S. Hershey Foundation. Milton Hershey School, established in 1910, is a residential school for girls and boys in financial need. The School serves children age 4 through high school graduation from throughout the United States, including inner city as well as rural poor. The School is non-sectarian and tuition-free. The student population is approximately 50 percent minority. MHS is endowed by the Milton Hershey Trust established by the chocolate magnate Milton S. Hershey. The School aspires to be a premier center of best practice, research, and thinking for the development of the full potential of children in financial need.</P>

<P>Dr. Lepley is a career educator. His extensive experience includes service as the Chief State School Officer for the state of Iowa. Prior to that, he served as a public school superintendent, principal, and teacher in several Iowa school systems. After graduating from Albia High School, Albia, Iowa, in 1963, he received his A.A. from Centerville Jr. College, his B.A. and M.S.E. from Northeast Missouri University, and Ed.Spec. and Ed.D. from Drake University.</P>

<P>Dr. Lepley is currently a member of the Great Lakes Pioneering Partners Leadership Team, which promotes the use of technology in classrooms and schools; New America School Development Corporation Education Advisory Panel, created to stimulate new school designs; the Agency for Instructional Technology Board of Directors, a non-profit entity that creates education software for schools, colleges, universities, and public broadcasting systems; and was the first President of the Board of Directors of the New Standards Project, a consortium of 20 states and several school districts committed to the creation of voluntary national content standards, new assessment strategies, and addressing educational equity issues.</P>

<P>Dr. Lepley has served on numerous Boards and Advisory Councils of organizations such as the U.S. Department of Education; Education Commission of the States (ECS); American Association of School Administrators (MSA); National Council of Accreditation of Teachers Education (NCATE); Council of Chief State School Officers (CCSSO); and the Association of Supervision and Curriculum Development (ASCD).</P>

<P>Dr. Lepley was selected to attend the historic national Education Summit called by President Bush and the national governors, led by then Governor Clinton, Governor Branstad of Iowa, and Governor Carroll Campbell of South Carolina.</P>

<P>Dr. Lepley has written numerous articles and has lectured on such topics as school transformation, partnership and networking, employees as partners in school reform, schools for 21 st Century, integration of special needs students, school finance reform, the role of national goals and standards, and the school leader as a change agent.</P>

<P>Dr. Lepley has received numerous awards and honors including the Midstates Toastmasters International Community Leadership Award; the Liberty Award by the Iowa Freedom Foundation; Outstanding Educator Award by Drake University; Outstanding Staff Development Award by the American Association of School Administrators.</P>

<P>Dr. Lepley's service to community boards and councils over the years has included the Boy Scouts, Children's Christian Home, Chamber of Commerce, YMCA, United Way, Hershey Rotary Club, and others.  He most recently was appointed to chair the Education Division Campaign for the Pennsylvania Capital Region United Way.</P>

<P>Dr. Lepley is married to Ginny Lepley. Bill and Ginny have two children and two granddaughters.</P>

<H5 ALIGN=RIGHT>Revised - August 8, 1995</H5>
<P>Dr. William Lepley may be reached via email at <A HREF="MAILTO:lepleyw@hershey.pvt.k12.pa.us">lepleyw@hershey.pvt.k12.pa.us</A></P>

<HR>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="/ait/aboard.htm">Return to Listing of AIT's Board Members</A>
</P>

<A HREF="/ait/aitcopy.htm">&copy; AIT </A>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
