<HEAD>
<TITLE>AIT Board of Directors - James R. Pagliarini</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0></A>
<H1>AIT Board of Directors</H1>
<HR>

<IMG SRC="pagliari.jpg" ALIGN=RIGHT VSPACE="10" ALIGN HSPACE="10">
<P><BR>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><I>James R. Pagliarini</I></H2>
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>CEO and General Manager KNPB-TV</H3>
<P><BR>

<HR>


<P>
Jim Pagliarini is the CEO and General Manager of public television station, KNPB/Channel 5 in Reno, Nevada, a position that he has held since 1982. Mr. Pagliarini, with a team from the University of Nevada, Reno, helped found KNPB/Channel 5 in 1983.</P>
<P>
In addition to his duties at KNPB, Mr. Pagliarini is serving his second term as a member of the Board of Directors of the Public Broadcasting Service (PBS) and is a member of the Board's Executive Cornmittee. He has also held the position of Vice Chair ofthe Board's Finance Committee during 1993-94. He has also served on numerous national task forces exploring and refining the business of public television, including the National Task Force on Future Funding, the PBS Task Force on Pricing Policies and Programming, and the Corporation for Public Broadcasting's (CPB) Television Policy Committee.</P>
<P>
He is a past Chairman of the Pacific Mountain Network Board of Directors; past President of the Nevada Public Broadcaster's Association, and served a two year term as the National Coordinator of public television's Small Station Association. Mr. Pagliarini also serves as a member of the Board of Directors of the Agency for Instructional Technology (AIT), a non-profit Canadian-U.S. corporation devoted to the production and development of educational media.</P>
<P>
Mr. Pagliarini received his undergraduate degree from Princeton University and his graduate degree from Temple University. He is married to Elizabeth Raymond, who is a professor of history at the University of Nevada.</P>

