<HEAD>
<TITLE>AIT Board of Directors - Werner Rogers</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0></A>
<H1>AIT Board of Directors</H1>
<HR>


<IMG SRC="rogers.jpg" ALIGN=RIGHT VSPACE="10">
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><I>Werner Rogers</I></H2>
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Executive Director<BR>Georgia Public Telecommunications Commission</H3>
<BR><HR>
<DL>
<H3>Address</H3>
<DD><P>Georgia Public Telecommunications Commission<BR>
1540 Stewart Avenue SW<BR>
Atlanta, Georgia 30310<BR>
<B>Telephone:</B> (404) 756-2410; <B>Fax:</B> (404) 756-2417<BR>
Send email to <A HREF="MAILTO:wrogers@gpb.org">wrogers@gpb.org</A>
</P>

<DT><H3>Personal Information</H3>
<DT><P><I><B>Date and Place of Birth</B></I>
<DD>December 5, 1941 &#151; Greenville, South Carolina</P>
<DT><P><I><B>Family</B></I>
<DD>Dr. Rogers is married to Judith Scherphorn Rogers, principal of Norcross High in
Gwinnett County. They have three daughters: Megan, who attends the University of Georgia; Katie, an eleventh grader; and Kristin, a ninth grader.</P>

<DT><H3>Academic Preparation</H3>
<DD><P>California State University, Long Beach &#151; B.A. 1964<BR>
University of Georgia, Athens &#151; M.Ed. 1972<BR>
University of Georgia, Athens &#151; Ed.S. 1973<BR>
University of Georgia, Athens &#151; Ed.D. 1976 </P>

<DT><H3>Professional Experience</H3>
<DT><UL TYPE="DISC">
<LI><P ALIGN=RIGHT><B>Executive Director, Georgia Public Telecommunications Commission &#151; January 1995 to Present</B></P>
<P>(The Commission oversees the operations of the nine-station Georgia Public Television (GPTV)
network, the 12-station Peach State Public Radio (PSPR) network and the PeachStar satellite,
distance learning network.)</P>
<LI>Georgia State Superintendent of Schools &#151; April 1986 to January 1995
<LI>Associate State Superintendent of Schools for Planning and Development,
<LI>Georgia Department of Education &#151; 1982 to 1986
<LI>Staff Assistant to State School Superintendent, Georgia Department of Education &#151; 1979 to 1982
<LI>Adjunct Professor, College of Education, University of Georgia, Athens &#151; 1977 to 1979
<LI>Director of Personnel, Clarke County Schools, Athens &#151; 1975 to 1979
<LI>Graduate Research Assistant, College of Education, University of Georgia, Athens &#151; 1973 to 1975
<LI>Community School Director, Clarke County Schools, Athens &#151; 1972 to 1973
<LI>Classroom Teacher and Vice Principal, Los Angeles, California &#151; 1966 to 1971
<LI>YMCA Youth Director, San Pedro, California &#151; 1963 to 1967
</UL>

<DT><H3>Military Service</H3>
<DD>U. S. Naval Reserve

<DT><H3>Professional Activities</H3>
<DD>Dr. Rogers is currently a member of the board of directors of the Agency for Instructional Technology, the Distance Learning Telemedicine Board, the Georgia Center for Advanced Telecommunications Technology (GCATT), the Southern Education Communications Association and the Satellite Education Resources Consortium (SERC). He is a member of the Organization of State Broadcast Executives, the Association of America's Public Television Stations and is a professional representative to the Public Broadcasting Service. He is also president of the Foundation for Public Broadcasting in Georgia.</P>
<P>
He was awarded an Honorary Doctor of Laws degree by Mercer University in 1994.</P>

<DT><H3>Community and Civic Activities</H3>
<DD><P>Dr. Rogers is on the Board of Directors of  Zoo Atlanta and Fernbank Natural History Museum and the Advisory Committee of the Auburn Avenue Research Library on African-American Culture and History.  He is a member of the Atlanta Rotary Club, the University of Georgia Alumni Association and the Georgia PTA.  Georgia Trend magazine named him one of the state's 100 Outstanding Georgians in 1991and again in 1994.  The family attends the Peachtree Presbyterian Church of Atlanta.</P>
</DL>

