<HEAD>
<TITLE>AIT Board of Directors - George Turner</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0></A>
<H1>AIT Board of Directors</H1>
<HR>


<IMG SRC="turner.jpg" ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE="10" ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE="12">
<BR>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>George Turner</H2>
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Corporate Vice President and General Manager<BR>
Logic and Analog Technologies Group<BR>
Motorola Semiconductor Products Sector<BR></H3>
<HR>
<P>
George joined Motorola in 1972 as a participant In Use Engineering Flotation Program at the Logic and Analog Technologies Group (LATG) headquarters in Mesa, Arizona.  After serving in numerous Product Engineering assignments, he was named Product Operations Manager and, in 1988, was promoted to Director of Reliability and Quality assurance for the group.
</P>
<P>
Appointed a Vice President, in 1990 George was named General Manaqer of the Logic Integrated Circuit Division within LATG. Three years later, he moved to the Communications, Power and Signal Technologies Group in Phoenix, Arizona, as General Manager of the Communications Semiconductor Products Division. He also was elected a Corporate Vice President of Motorola, Inc.
</P>
<P>
George holds a bachelors degree in Electrical Engineering from the University of New Mexico.</P>

<H5 ALIGN=RIGHT>Communications &amp; Public Relations<BR>
February 1996</H5>
<HR>

<table border=0>
<tr><td>Date:</td><td>Februay 21, 1996</td></tr>
<tr><td>To:</td><td> Executive/Professional Briefing List</td></tr>
<tr><td>From:</td><td>Tommy George/Murray Goldman</td></tr>
<tr><td><I>Subject:</I></td><td><I>Leadership Appointment - Logic and Analog Technology Group General Manager</I></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<P>
Recently, Gary Johnson was selected to lead the Sector's effort to modernize and streamline our service and logistics capabilities--one part of our initiative to enhance responsiveness for SPS customers, worldwide. We are now pleased to announce that George Turner will replace Gary Johnson as General Manager of the Logic &amp; Analog Technology Group (LATG) headquartered in Tempe, Arizona.
</P>
<P>
George's background and leadership experience in a variety of functions and organizations, combined with his ability and willingness to generate results through cross-Sector teamwork, qualify him for this key promotion.
</P>
<P>
George has been a key contributor to SPS Foror a number of years in LATG prior to his most recent assignment as General Manager of our  Communications Semiconductor Products Division within our Communication, Power and Signal Technologies Group. During his tenure in LATG George served as Product Engineering Manager and General Manager of the Logic IC Division and as Group Director of Reliability &amp; Quality.
</P>
<P>
Please join us in congratulating George on his promotion to this significant responsibility, not only to the leadership position of a major SPS business, but also to a key membership role on the Sector staff leaders team.
</P>
<BR>
<P>Tommy George<BR>Murray Goldman</P>

