<TITLE>AIT Board of Directors - Gene Wilhoit</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0></A>
<H1>AIT Board of Directors</H1>
<HR>


<IMG SRC="wilhoit.jpg" ALIGN=RIGHT VSPACE="10" ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE="10">
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Gene Wilhoit</H2>
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Director<BR>Departmnet of Education<BR>State of Arkansas</H3>

<HR>
<P>
Gene Wilhoit was appointed by Governor Jim Guy Tucker and the State Board of Education to serve as the Director of the Arkansas State Department of Education on September 7,1993. The Arkansas Department of Education employs approximately 300 people and operates with an annual budget of over 1.3 billion dollars. The Department oversees the 311 local districts which serve 440,000 students.
</P>
<P>Previous to this time he served as executive director of the Association of State Boards of Education.  Mr. Wilhoit did Graduate Study in Educational Administration at West Virginia College of Graduate Studies.  He received his Master of Arts in Teaching, Political Science, Economics, Educational Chage Theory at Indiana University; and Bachelor of Arts in History and Economics at Georgetown College.
</P>
<P>
Prior to his experience in the Arkansas Department of Education, Mr. Wilhoit served as: </P>
<UL>
<LI>Executive Director, National Association of State Boards of Education in Virginia
<LI>Program Director in the Indiana Department of Public Instruction
<LI>Special Assistant in the United States Department of Education
<LI>Adjunct Professor of Education, Indiana University
<LI>Social Studies Department Head in Indiana
<LI>Social Studies Teacher in Indiana and Ohio
</UL>

<P>
Widely admired for his skill as a facilitator and his ability to help groups develop education plans, he is also well known in education circles for his understanding and analysis of difficult issues and his comprehensive vision for education reform. His primary work has
been to make schools better for all children.
</P>
<P>
He lives in Little Rock with his wife, Becky, and their two sons, Christopher and Jason. He has a married daughter, Kara, who lives with her husband in Indiana.
</P>
<P ALIGN=RIGHT>
Gene Wilhoit can be reached via electronic mail at <A HREF="MAILTO:dirade@loki.k12.ar.us">dirade@loki.k12.ar.us</A>.
</P>
