<HEAD>
<TITLE>About AIT</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD>
<TD>


<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif"></P>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Agency for Instructional Technology</H2>

<P>The Agency for Instructional Technology is a nonprofit U.S.-Canadian education agency, founded in 1962, whose mission is to foster learning for pre-K through adult students.  AIT develops, acquires, and distributes quality technology-based instructional resources and services; and it provides leadership to the educational technology policy community.  AIT is the headquarters of TECHNOS Press, home of the annual AIT Distinguished Fellows Program and publisher of <I>TECHNOS: Quarterly for Education and Technology</I>.</P>

<P>AIT products include video programming, interactive videodiscs, computer software, CD-ROMs, and supporting print.  AIT materials, which comprise 40% of all broadcast video classroom programming in the U.S. and Canada, are used on six continents, reaching nearly 34 million students in North American classrooms each year.  AIT services include workshops and <B>AIT.Net</B>, an online interactive service for educators.</P>

<P>Since 1970, the Agency has cooperatively produced more than  39 curriculum packages through the consortium process it pioneered.  Major project funding comes from state provincial, and local departments of education, federal and private institutions, corporate sponsors, and other partners.</P>
<HR>


<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD WIDTH="40%" ALIGN=CENTER><H2>AIT&#146;s Mission</H2></TD>
<TD><TABLE>
<TR><TD COLSPAN=2><I>The mission of AIT, a non-profit corporation, is to foster learning by</I></TD></TR>
<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif" VSPACE="6"></TD><TD><I>developing, acquiring and distributing quality electronic technology-based resources and services, and</I></TD></TR>
<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG SRC="/images/dot_bl.gif" VSPACE="6"></TD><TD><I>providing leadership to the educational technology policy community</I></TD></TR>
</TABLE></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<BR><BR>


<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD WIDTH="40%" ALIGN=CENTER><H2>The People of AIT</H2></TD>
<TD>
<DL>
<DT><A HREF = "/ait/aboard.htm">AIT&#146;s Board of Directors</A><BR>
<DD>AIT&#146;s 17 member Board of Directors provides the Agency with direction and guidance, and is composed of leaders from all segments of the education and business communities.
<DT><BR><A HREF = "/ait/astaff.htm">AIT&#146;s Employees</A><BR>
<DD>AIT maintains a staff of approximately 50-personnel who are helping the Agency to develop more materials, offer more services, and distribute more information than ever before.
</DL>
</TD></TR></TABLE>


